The paper deals with game models and category theory, which are topics commonly found in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the notion of innocence, which is a concept in theoretical computer science and falls under the cs.THEORY sub-category. The use of sheaves and plays in the paper suggests a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of non-determinism and probabilistic branching suggests a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
